Sasarin spouted a stream of flames, this tall slark person set a small patch of forest ablaze, and then hovered above it, observing the timing. It was strange that when he slowed down, the strange screeching sounds coming from behind also stopped. Sasarin forgot that there was a passenger on his back.
"Please, Tnuuk, you weren't a slark person before!"
"Being swept away by a massive pink dragon while flying is a different story!"
"Good, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly disagreed with Nisi's statement, he looked paler than usual, his claws had dug deep into Sasarin's back, drawing blood from the slark person, but Sasarin seemed not to care. Despite this, Sasarin realized he had scared his new friend, so he found a clearing to land.
“Sorry sorry, I can smell something. I need to handle this!”
“Are you going to drag us along too?” Tnuuk climbed down from Sasarin's back and slid down his tail to the ground, asking sharply. “We left Rethvik behind! We abandoned that strong and fierce giant! How will he find us?”
“He'll figure it out...” Nisi muttered. “Rethvik is slow to react, but not stupid.”
“Will Rethvik drive?”
Nisi blinked and turned to Tnuuk. “Of course he will drive.”
“Have you ever seen Rethvik drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like Kayel's. He only started driving to work because you always drove us to school. He only has a bicycle.”
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasarin suddenly burst into laughter, but no one knew what he was laughing about. Sasarin took a while to calm down.
“Sorry, sorry, I was just imagining this... your big friend in armor, riding a bicycle designed for Tenok kids. The image was hilarious! I wish I had telepathic abilities. This idea is so interesting! I have to remember it!”
Kayel also laughed because he could imagine what Sasarin was thinking. “Okay, okay. But what did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?”
Sasarin let out a hum, flew away quickly, and then came back, dropping a corpse in front of Niix. It was an Orosarak, a rare white and gold dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. “Another one died. I heard their cries. Smelled their blood. I have to protect them, hunt down the killer. This is Isin's will. Those creatures are nearby.”
A powerful slark person suddenly froze. Nisi and Kayel also froze, their attention drawn to a hole on the edge of the clearing. A massive and black thing was staring at them, making a hissing sound. It suddenly spread its two huge wings, charging forward with a target fixed on Sasarin, completely disregarding the three small creatures in its way. Kayel and Tnuuk barely managed to dodge aside, but Nisi found himself being knocked to the ground, almost being flung onto Sasarin.
Sasarin grabbed Nisi with its long and agile tail, throwing her onto its back, and then took off into the air. The black creature with two wings quickly chased after it.
Kayel grunted, pulling out a gun from behind and opening a bag, taking out a bullet belt. He hung the bullet belt across his chest for easy access, but quickly realized that Nisi, Sasarin, and the creature were nowhere to be seen.
“Hey, Tnuuk, can you transform into a flying animal?” Kayel asked.
“Do you want to go after them?”
“Enough talk.”
“But... one of them is a giant monster!”
“So what? I've got a powerful rifle in my hands, and I can open fire at any time. I just need to see it, and I can take it down.”
Tnuuk hesitated for a moment, then took a step back, giving himself some space. With a low, slightly pained groan, Tnuuk's body stretched out, his fur turning into scales, his arms turning into wings. He quickly transformed into a ordinary light blue slark person, but his eyes remained red.
“Come on.”
Tnuuk now looks like a relatively ordinary Slark, with scales on his back arranged in an orderly fashion and a pair of sharp spikes, making it easier for Kayel to grab onto him. Tnuuk took a long time to fly, but once he took off, he quickly adjusted his direction and tried to catch up.
However, Tnuuk and Kayel soon realized they weren't the only ones with an opponent. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tnuuk barely avoided collision.
“I guess this is the other terrifying creature Raneck was worried about?” Kayel furrowed his brow, trying to shoot at the second creature, but missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tnuuk didn't respond, as he was busy flying towards Niix and Sasarin, despite the other creature chasing them. Kayel clumsily turned around, facing the creature. The creature was chasing them, and Kayel thought this was good news, as it would be easier for him to aim and shoot. Two bullets pierced the creature's upper wing, and it screamed in pain, disappearing into the forest. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he thought it definitely couldn't keep up.
In front, Sasarin was frantically waving his body, spraying flames at the black creature, while Niix desperately tried to hold onto Sasarin to prevent him from falling. Although this creature was definitely injured, it seemed to have been enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs didn't cause much damage. Sasarin stabilized his body, and Niix took advantage of the opportunity to pull out her weapon, a shotgun she trusted. Of course, the shotgun wouldn't be effective against this creature, but the scattered bullets might at least scare it off.
